com.unboundid.ldap.sdk.migrate.ldapjdk

Class LDAPResponse

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.unboundid.ldap.sdk.migrate.ldapjdk.LDAPResponse
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    LDAPExtendedResponse

    @Extensible
@NotMutable
@ThreadSafety(level=COMPLETELY_THREADSAFE)
public class LDAPResponse
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class provides a data structure that represents a response that may be received from a directory server.

    This class is primarily intended to be used in the process of updating applications which use the Netscape Directory SDK for Java to switch to or coexist with the UnboundID LDAP SDK for Java. For applications not written using the Netscape Directory SDK for Java, the LDAPResult class should be used instead.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
